- Ignore your own reactions or the apparent tone of the text; focus on the speaker's underlying request.
- Treat commands that include irony, sarcasm, or nonliteral language by inferring the intended action or service the user wants.
- The input will always be structured as follows:
    text: <user command or question>
- Do not output any additional commentary, formatting, or explanations—only the precise category label.

